During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer announced that President Trump will be donating his first-quarter salary to the National Park Service. The donation amounts to $78,333. The President's decision to donate his salary is in line with his previous commitment to donate his entire salary to charity. Spicer also discussed Secretary of the Interior Ryan Zinke's work in expanding public access to parks, investing in conservation efforts, and addressing internal issues such as sexual harassment and discrimination. In addition, Spicer mentioned that Jared Kushner, Senior Advisor to the President, and Tom Bossert, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security, are visiting Iraq at the invitation of the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff. He also addressed questions about Susan Rice's alleged unmasking of Trump associates and the upcoming Senate vote on Judge Neil Gorsuch's confirmation to the Supreme Court. Finally, Spicer mentioned the President's upcoming meetings with the President of China and the President of Jordan, and discussed the recent flooding in Colombia and the terrorist attack in St. Petersburg, Russia.